headline.main: CHURCHILL WORKS ON 67TH BIRTHDAY; It Is Just Another Long, Hard Sunday for Prime Minister -- He Prepares Speech

lead_paragraph: LONDON, Nov. 30 (AP) -- Deep in war problems, including preparation of a major speech to be given soon in the Commons on all-out conscription of men and women, Prime Minister Winaton Churchill took little part today in a world-wide observance of his sixty-seventh birthday.
abstract: Officials and observers: U S Cong group with Churchill, illus
